HEADWORD: Rejectamenta
<hw>Re*jec`ta*men"ta</hw> <pr>(r?-j?k`t?-m?n"ta)</pr>, <pos>n.
pl.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr. L. <ets>rejectare</ets>, v. intens. fr.
<ets>rejicere</ets>. See <er>Reject</er>.]</ety> <def>Things thrown out
or away; especially, things excreted by a living organism.</def>
